îóŸRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-12-14-twin0277.mdŸ@5c4dba89bae60288995446843aaa525b6a2393f0eb951bb8883f6bfa195f244dπThis week in Nushell #277ëßNushell⁄fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14571] fixed 64-bit hex number parsing
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14541] updated reedline
, and reverted some buggy PRs (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14560] 1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14580] 2
)
sgvictorino 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14577] returned const values from 
``scope variables``
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14573] added support for raw strings in match patterns
rikukiix 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14570] fixed 
``exec``
 to decrement SHLVL correctly
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14569] updated dependencies
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14407] added 
``-l/--long``
 flag to du, removed 
``-a/--all``
 flag
NotTheDr01ds did lots of polish for configuration: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14568] updated sample and scaffold files
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14566] set empty 
``ENV_CONVERSIONS``
 record by default
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14553] allowed both NU_PLUGIN_DIRS const and env at the same time
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14549] used const NU_LIB_DIRS in startup
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14509] only ran 
``from_string``
 conversion on strings
RobbingDaHood made some parser fixes for comments: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14562] 1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14548] 2
cptpiepmatz 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14530] fixed 
``table``
 command when targeting WASM
132ikl 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14526] removed grid icons deprecation warning
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14490] changed 
``help commands``
 to use name from scope instead of the name from the declaration
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14483] made 
``timeit``
 take only closures as an argument
